COMPONENT NAME: LKM Spark to File COMPONENT VERSION: 1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.1.3.0.1 or above
DESCRIPTION This KM will store data into a file from a Spark Python variable and can be defined on the AP between the execution units, source technology Spark Python, target technology File.
The storage function to be used to load/store data

Choose one of storage functions to store data. "saveAsTextFile" is used to store the data into hdfs, a local file system or any Hadoop-supported file system URI. "newAPIHadoopFile" is used to store the data to a Hadoop file with an arbitrary new API InputFormat. "saveAsHadoopFile" is used to store data to a Hadoop file with an arbitrary InputFormat. "saveAsSequenceFile" is used to store data into key-value pairs within Java.

Specify a fully qualified class name for writing the data.
Example: org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.lib.input.TextOutputFormat
fully qualified classname of key Writable class
Specify a fully qualified class for keys. Examples: org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable (default) org.apache.hadoop.io.Text
fully qualified classname of value Writable class

Specify a fully qualified class for values.
Examples: org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable org.apache.hadoop.io.Text (default)
fully qualified classname of key converter class
Specify a class for key converter.
fully qualified classname of value converter class
Specify a class for value converter.
